cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper involves the recording and preprocessing of a new dataset of simultaneous eye-tracking and electroencephalography during natural reading and during annotation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category deals with the study of natural language processing and computational linguistics, which is relevant to the linguistic annotation task in this paper. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the study of algorithms and models that enable computers to learn from data, which is relevant to the preprocessing and analysis of the dataset. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category deals with the study of neural networks and other computational models inspired by biological systems, which is relevant to the electroencephalography recordings in this paper. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): This sub-category deals with the study of the impact of computing on society and vice versa, which is relevant to the potential applications of the dataset in fields such as education and psychology. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): This sub-category deals with the study of the interaction between humans and computers, which is relevant to the eye-tracking recordings in this paper.
